cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a process for training an object detector for robotic grasping and manipulation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves using synthetic images for training, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses domain adaptation through adversarial training, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves object classification and localization, which are also common topics in computer vision and machine learning (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of activation maps to guide the search for 6D poses, which falls under the category of graphics (cs.GR).
